# ============================================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION — choose ONE option below:
# ============================================================

# OPTION A: Local PostgreSQL
# 1. Install PostgreSQL from https://www.postgresql.org/download/windows/
# 2. Create the database: psql -U postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE openlab;"
# 3. Run migrations: npm run db:init
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:yourpassword@localhost:5432/openlab

# OPTION B: Supabase (free cloud PostgreSQL — recommended if no local Postgres)
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com → New Project
# 2. Go to Settings → Database → Connection string → URI
# 3. Paste your connection string below:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.[YOUR-REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres
# 4. After setting the URL, run: npm run db:init

